<LP>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio -- Max &amp; Erma's Restaurants Inc. said its
board authorized the repurchase from time to time through
March 15, of as much as $1 million of its common shares.
   The stock will be repurchased on the open market or
through privately negotiated transactions, the company said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said it considers its stock undervalued. In
over-the-counter trading Friday, Max &amp; Erma's rose 12.5 cents
to $4.25.
   Max &amp; Erma's said it has 3.2 million shares outstanding.
Over the past year, the stock has traded as high as $8.50 and
as low as $3.875.
</TEXT>
